main event: A woman observed a square, brownish object moving in a circular motion at slow speed in Rock Garden, Tennessee on September 9, 1955.
interesting points: The object was observed for 10-15 minutes,The object appeared to be solid and was moving from north to northeast before disappearing behind trees,There was no sound heard from the object during the sighting,Multiple military and civilian aircraft in the area reported no sightings or unusual phenomena,Weather conditions were clear at the time of the sighting.
witness description: a 31-year-old housewife with no formal training
